message.entry: Provide a datetime or duration row times vector, a duration or calendarDuration time step, or a positive numeric sample rate to create timetable.
Provide datetime or duration vector for row times to create timetable. To convert table to timetable, use TABLE2TIMETABLE.

You might have intended "{0}" to specify a parameter name. However, the timetable constructor requires parameter names to be specified as character vectors. Use timetable(..., {0}=Value) or timetable(..., ''{0}'', Value) instead.
Specify a row times vector, time step, or sample rate when preallocating a timetable to a specified size.
Specify times for subscripting as datetime or duration.
Row times must be datetime or duration vector.
New row times must be {0} vector.
Timetable row subscript must be a numeric, logical, or datetime array, or a timerange subscripter.
Timetable row subscript must be a numeric, logical, or duration array, or a timerange subscripter.

Numeric array indices must be positive integers. If you intended to select rows of the timetable by time, use DURATION, MILLISECONDS, SECONDS, MINUTES, HOURS, DAYS, or YEARS to convert from numeric to duration.
Deleting row times from timetable is not supported.
RowTimes property must contain one time for each row in the timetable.
RowTimes property must contain one time for each row being reassigned.
Timetable does not contain a row for the time ''{0}''.

entry.note: Do NOT add period ('.') at the end - it is intentionally left out.

Concatenating a timetable whose row times are {0} with a timetable whose row times are {1} is not supported.
Unrecognized timetable variable name ''{0}''. If you intended to access the row times, use ''{1}'' for this timetable instead.
Unrecognized timetable variable name ''{0}''. Names are case sensitive. You may have intended to access the timetable's row times as ''{1}''.
Specify either a row times vector, or a time step, or a sample rate, but not more than one.
Specify either the time step as a scalar duration or calendarDuration, or the sample rate as a positive scalar.
The sample rate must be a positive numeric scalar, specified in Hz.
The time step must be a scalar duration or calendarDuration.

The time step must be a scalar duration or calendarDuration. Convert a numeric value to a duration using SECONDS, MINUTES, HOURS, DAYS, or YEARS, or convert to a calendarDuration using CALDAYS, CALWEEKS, CALMONTHS, CALQUARTERS, or CALYEARS.
The start time must be a scalar duration or datetime.
Events property must be an event table.
The attached event table's row times and the corresponding timetable's row times must both have time zones, or must both be unzoned.
The attached event table's row times must be the same data type as the corresponding timetable's row times.
The start time must be a scalar duration or datetime. Convert a numeric value to a duration using SECONDS, MINUTES, HOURS, DAYS, or YEARS, or convert using DATETIME.
Specify the start time as a datetime when the time step is a calendarDuration.
A calendarDuration time step must be made up of only one calendar unit such as days or months. Use CALDAYS, CALWEEKS, CALMONTHS, CALQUARTERS, or CALYEARS to create a calendarDuration time step.
''SamplingRate'' is no longer supported. Use ''SampleRate'' instead.
Use timeseries2timetable to convert timeseries objects into timetables.

To construct a timetable, specify both data and duration row times vector, a duration or calendarDuration time step, or a positive numeric sample rate to create timetable. If you meant to construct a timetable from the signals in a Simulink.SimulationData.Dataset, use EXTRACTTIMETABLE.
